      • getPrice

        public double getPrice(java.lang.String stockSymbol,
                       java.time.LocalDate date)
        Return the price of a stock at certain day. If stockSymbol is null or empty string, or date is null, this method will throw IllegalArgumentException. For a valid stock, if there is no value at date, this will return 0. The price that get returned is the open price of that day.
        Specified by:
        getPrice in interface IGetPrice
        Parameters:
        stockSymbol - given stock symbol
        date - certain date of price

        the price of a stock at certain day
